title: For Sale:  Karesuando Knife
postcontent:
This is a very fine piece of traditional handcraft made in the Swedish part of Lapland. Karesuandos manufacture of hunting, fishing and handicraft product is performed in Karesuando, located in the Arctic tundra. The products used can be found in the harsh Arctic climate. Raw materials are taken from the surrounding nature. Leather, horns and bones of reindeer, and birch wood are the most common components.

The Blade is 3 1/2” long, and 11/16” wide is Very Sharp and is made from high quality Sandvik 12C27 stainless "surgical" steel (HRC 57). The blade extends with an internal tang that stretches approx 2.5" into the handle and is secured very firmly so that it will not come loose. In fact 
Karesuando offers a Life-time Guarantee that if the blade comes loose you will get an new knife straight away! Basically the blade will never come loose! The internal tang design is very beneficial from a weight perspective. 

The Handle is made from oiled curly birch and reindeer antler. The Sheath is made from vegetable tanned cow hide leather and has a reindeer leather belt hanger attached to it and is decorated with a traditional pattern.

This is a very special knife, and although it has been made to be used, it is also a great collectable item.

This knife is new.

postcontent:

It also has a tapco black wood stock as well. This saiga runs flawlessly and has never had any issues functioning. This saiga is just like any AK should be. It is extremely reliable and shoots tight groups at 100 yards. Included is one ten round magazine. I prefer a cash sale but I will considered some trades. This saiga is well worth my asking price. I have seen them sell for much more. If you are looking for a beautiful russian akm then look no further. I am downsizing my collection a bit so this one must go.
